      </h2>
      
      <div class="overflow-x-auto">
        <table class="w-full text-sm">
          <thead>
            <tr class="border-b border-slate-dark">
              <th class="text-left py-3 px-4 text-text-muted font-medium">File</th>
              <th class="text-left py-3 px-4 text-text-muted font-medium">What It Scans</th>
              <th class="text-left py-3 px-4 text-text-muted font-medium">Recommended</th>
            </tr>
          </thead>
          <tbody class="text-text-secondary">
            <tr class="border-b border-slate-dark/50">
              <td class="py-3 px-4 font-mono text-araptus-glow">package.json</td>
              <td class="py-3 px-4">Direct dependencies only</td>
              <td class="py-3 px-4"><span class="px-2 py-1 rounded text-xs bg-warning/15 text-warning border border-warning/30">Quick check</span></td>
            </tr>
            <tr class="border-b border-slate-dark/50">
              <td class="py-3 px-4 font-mono text-info">pnpm-lock.yaml</td>
              <td class="py-3 px-4">ALL dependencies (deep scan)</td>
              <td class="py-3 px-4"><span class="px-2 py-1 rounded text-xs bg-safe/15 text-safe border border-safe/30">‚úì Best for pnpm</span></td>
            </tr>
            <tr class="border-b border-slate-dark/50">
              <td class="py-3 px-4 font-mono text-info">package-lock.json</td>
              <td class="py-3 px-4">ALL dependencies (deep scan)</td>
              <td class="py-3 px-4"><span class="px-2 py-1 rounded text-xs bg-safe/15 text-safe border border-safe/30">‚úì Best for npm</span></td>
            </tr>
            <tr>
              <td class="py-3 px-4 font-mono text-info">yarn.lock</td>
              <td class="py-3 px-4">ALL dependencies (deep scan)</td>
              <td class="py-3 px-4"><span class="px-2 py-1 rounded text-xs bg-safe/15 text-safe border border-safe/30">‚úì Best for yarn</span></td>
            </tr>
          </tbody>
        </table>
      </div>
      
      <div class="mt-4 p-4 rounded-lg bg-info/5 border border-info/20">
        <p class="text-text-secondary text-sm flex items-start gap-2">
          <span class="text-lg">üí°</span>
          <span>
            <strong class="text-text-primary">Pro tip:</strong> Upload your lock file for the most thorough scan. 
            Supply chain attacks like <strong class="text-warning">Shai-Hulud</strong> often hide in transitive dependencies 
            that only appear in lock files, not in your package.json.
          </span>
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>

    <!-- Campaign Info - Enhanced Timeline -->
    <div class="mt-16">
      <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-text-primary mb-2 text-center">
        Recent Supply Chain Attacks
      </h2>
      <p class="text-text-muted text-center mb-8">
        Our scanner tracks {CAMPAIGN_COUNT} major attack campaigns from 2025
      </p>
      
      <div class="space-y-4">
        <!-- Shai-Hulud -->
        <div class="card p-6 border-alert/30 hover:border-alert/50 transition-colors relative overflow-hidden">
          <div class="absolute top-0 left-0 w-1 h-full bg-alert"></div>
          <div class="flex items-start gap-4">
            <div class="w-12 h-12 rounded-xl bg-alert/10 flex items-center justify-center flex-shrink-0">
              <span class="text-2xl">üêõ</span>
            </div>
            <div class="flex-1">
              <div class="flex flex-wrap items-center gap-2 mb-1">
                <h3 class="font-semibold text-text-primary text-lg">Shai-Hulud Malware</h3>
                <span class="badge-critical text-xs font-medium uppercase">Critical</span>
                <span class="text-text-muted text-sm">Sept-Nov 2025</span>
              </div>
              <p class="text-text-secondary text-sm leading-relaxed">
                Self-replicating worm that infected <strong class="text-alert">700+ packages</strong> with 2M+ weekly downloads. 
                Harvests npm credentials and developer tokens by modifying package.json files. 
                <span class="text-warning">Resurged in November 2025</span> affecting Zapier, PostHog, and Ethereum ecosystem.
              </p>
              <div class="mt-3 flex flex-wrap gap-2">
                <span class="px-2 py-1 rounded text-xs bg-slate-mid/30 text-text-muted">@ctrl/tinycolor</span>
                <span class="px-2 py-1 rounded text-xs bg-slate-mid/30 text-text-muted">prebuild-install</span>
                <span class="px-2 py-1 rounded text-xs bg-slate-mid/30 text-text-muted">node-gyp-build</span>
                <span class="text-text-muted text-xs">+697 more</span>
              </div>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>

        <!-- Credential Phishing -->
        <div class="card p-6 border-alert/30 hover:border-alert/50 transition-colors relative overflow-hidden">
          <div class="absolute top-0 left-0 w-1 h-full bg-alert"></div>
          <div class="flex items-start gap-4">
